The paper deals with the theory of learning in deep neural networks, specifically focusing on the generalization abilities of deep neural classifiers in both single task and multitask settings. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses techniques from statistical physics to analyze the dynamics of the neural networks, which could potentially fall under the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of input features on task performance, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
